description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit an experienced Cardiac Nurse to join our Cardiac Nursing Team. The successful applicant will join our established Coronary Heart Disease Nursing Department to work autonomously across our pathways to ensure the delivery of high quality, patient focused care to those with both acute presentations and long term cardiac conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cardiac Assessment Nurses lead on the management of patients across a variety of both inpatient and outpatient pathways. Our award winning Cardiac Assessment Unit is supported by a Cardiologist but as an Assessment Nurse you will use your knowledge and skills to work autonomously to manage patients with a variety of cardiac conditions that can be managed through this ambulatory setting (e.g. Low risk chest pain, new onset AF, IV. diuretics for patients with early decompensated heart failure).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunities to working alongside colleagues within the Emergency Department (ED) you will provide clinical assessment and support in the care and treatment of a diverse and undetermined caseload of patients with cardiac conditions in ED, you will have opportunities to further sub specialise into areas such as Cardiac Rehabilitation, Post MI clinics or Arrhythmia clinics .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will have experience of providing care to those with acute conditions. Applicants should hold a relevant post qualification cardiac course and/or be able to demonstrate evidence of study and working to Masters level. Physical Assessment Skills and being an Independent Non-Medical Prescriber are desirable but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department is focused on supporting staff develop with an induction program, a named medical mentor to support in competencies, PGD’s and transcribing along with a period of supernumerary practice. There is also on-going opportunities for career progression with roles including ANP/ ACP or Consultant Nurse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want to be part of this dynamic team, are motivated, deliver excellence in care, respect and responsibility then this is the role for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits are welcomed and encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Andrew Hunter on 01384 456111 ext 3431 or Matron Marie Banner bleep 5094.&lt;/p&gt;
